## Overview

This guide outlines the end-to-end process for registering your application, managing credentials, and performing interactive testing for the Bankrate Developer platform. API keys are required to authenticate your requests and should be handled as sensitive credentials.

---

## Creating Your API Key

To begin integrating, you must generate a key through the Developer Portal.

1. Click the **APIs** button in the top navigation bar to view all APIs.
2. Click **View APIs** for the API you wish to generate a key for.
3. Click **Use this API**.
4. Click **+ New Application**.
5. **Label your application:** Use a descriptive name following the naming pattern of `[Organization/Partner]-[API]` (e.g., Bankrate-ProductsAPI).
6. **Add a description:** Describe what your key will be used for.
7. Select **This is a team owned application**. We highly recommend making every application a team owned one.
8. Select your team from the drop down menu.
9. Click **Create and use API**.
10. The next screen shows your credential: Make sure to copy and save in a safe place, such as a Secret Management tool, as it is only shown once.
11. Add a custom name to your application and select **update credentials**.

---

## Testing Your API Key

1. Navigate to the APIs section and select the API you generated your key for.
2. Select which endpoint you will connect to (e.g., Home Lending).
3. On the right hand side, you should see a box labeled **Authentication**. This is where you will enter your API key.

